%% Claude Code IDE Bridge — Bidirectional Communication Architecture
%% Source: /bridge/replBridge.ts, bridgeMain.ts, bridgeMessaging.ts, bridgeApi.ts

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant IDE as IDE Extension<br/>(VS Code / JetBrains)
    participant WEB as Claude.ai Web UI
    participant SRV as Session-Ingress Server<br/>(Anthropic)
    participant BRIDGE as Bridge Core<br/>(replBridge.ts + bridgeMain.ts)
    participant REPL as REPL / QueryEngine<br/>(useReplBridge hook)

    Note over BRIDGE,SRV: ══ PHASE 1: Environment Registration ══

    BRIDGE->>+SRV: POST /v1/environments/bridge<br/>{oauth_token}
    SRV-->>-BRIDGE: {environment_id, environment_secret}
    BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Save bridge pointer<br/>(~/.claude/bridge-pointer-{dir}.json)

    BRIDGE->>+SRV: POST /v1/code/sessions<br/>{oauth_token}
    SRV-->>-BRIDGE: {session.id} (cse_* or session_*)

    Note over BRIDGE,SRV: ══ PHASE 2: Work Polling ══

    loop Poll for work (exponential backoff, 2s→120s)
        BRIDGE->>+SRV: GET /v1/environments/{id}/work<br/>{environmentSecret}
        alt No work available
            SRV-->>BRIDGE: 204 No Content
            BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Backoff sleep<br/>(capacityWake can interrupt)
        else Work received
            SRV-->>-BRIDGE: {workId, ingressToken (JWT),<br/>use_code_sessions: bool}
        end
    end

    Note over BRIDGE,SRV: ══ PHASE 3: Transport Setup ══

    alt v1 Protocol (use_code_sessions = false)
        BRIDGE->>+SRV: WebSocket: ws://host/v1/session_ingress/ws/{sessionId}<br/>Bearer {oauthToken}
        SRV-->>-BRIDGE: WebSocket connected
        Note over BRIDGE,SRV: Outbound via HTTP POST<br/>Inbound via WebSocket
    else v2 Protocol (use_code_sessions = true)
        BRIDGE->>+SRV: POST /worker/register<br/>{JWT}
        SRV-->>-BRIDGE: {worker_epoch}
        BRIDGE->>+SRV: SSE: GET /worker/events/stream<br/>{JWT, initialSequenceNum}
        SRV-->>-BRIDGE: SSE stream opened
        Note over BRIDGE,SRV: Outbound via POST /worker/events<br/>Inbound via SSE stream
    end

    BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: FlushGate.start()<br/>(buffer new messages during flush)
    BRIDGE->>SRV: writeBatch(initialMessages)<br/>(conversation history)
    BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: FlushGate.end() → drain buffered
    BRIDGE-->>REPL: onStateChange('connected')

    Note over IDE,REPL: ══ PHASE 4: Bidirectional Message Flow ══

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over IDE,REPL: IDE → CLI (Inbound)
        IDE->>SRV: User prompt from IDE
        SRV->>BRIDGE: SDKMessage {type:'user', message, uuid}
        BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: bridgeMessaging.ts:<br/>Parse → Dedup (BoundedUUIDSet) → Route
        alt type = 'user'
            BRIDGE->>REPL: onInboundMessage(prompt)<br/>→ enqueue as new user turn
        else type = 'control_request'
            Note over BRIDGE: Subtypes:<br/>initialize, set_model,<br/>set_permission_mode, interrupt
            BRIDGE->>REPL: Execute control callback
            REPL-->>BRIDGE: Control response
            BRIDGE->>SRV: SDKControlResponse {request_id, response}
        else type = 'control_response'
            BRIDGE->>REPL: onPermissionResponse()<br/>(permission decision from server)
        end
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over IDE,REPL: CLI → IDE (Outbound)
        REPL->>BRIDGE: writeMessage(SDKMessage)<br/>{type:'assistant', content, uuid}
        BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Add uuid to recentPostedUUIDs<br/>(echo filtering)
        alt v1 transport
            BRIDGE->>SRV: HTTP POST /v1/session_ingress/{sessionId}<br/>{SDKMessage + session_id}
        else v2 transport
            BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /worker/events<br/>{SDKMessage batch via CCRClient}
        end
        SRV->>IDE: Forward to IDE/Web UI
        SRV->>WEB: Forward to Web UI
    end

    Note over BRIDGE,SRV: ══ PHASE 5: Keep-Alive & Reconnection ══

    loop Heartbeat (every 20s, v2 only)
        BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /worker/heartbeat<br/>{JWT}
        alt 200 OK
            SRV-->>BRIDGE: Lease extended (300s TTL)
        else 401/403 (JWT expired)
            SRV-->>BRIDGE: Auth error
            BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: onHeartbeatFatal()<br/>→ kill transport
            BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: reconnectSession()
        end
    end

    loop Work heartbeat (every 60s)
        BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/environments/{id}/heartbeat<br/>{workId}
        SRV-->>BRIDGE: Lease extended
    end

    Note over BRIDGE,SRV: ══ Reconnection Strategies ══

    alt Transport close (code ≠ 1000)
        BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: handleTransportPermanentClose()
        BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Capture lastSequenceNum

        alt Strategy 1: Reconnect-in-place
            BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/environments/bridge<br/>{reuseEnvironmentId}
            SRV-->>BRIDGE: Same environment_id
            BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/bridge/reconnect<br/>{sessionId}
            SRV-->>BRIDGE: Reconnected (preserve history)
        else Strategy 2: Fresh session
            BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/sessions/{id}/archive
            BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/code/sessions (new)
            SRV-->>BRIDGE: New session_id
            BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Reset seq=0, clear UUIDs
            BRIDGE->>SRV: Re-flush initial messages
        end
    end

    Note over BRIDGE,SRV: ══ PHASE 6: Teardown ══

    REPL->>BRIDGE: Session ending
    BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Abort poll loop
    BRIDGE->>SRV: writeMessage({type:'result'})<br/>(session archival signal)
    BRIDGE->>SRV: transport.flush() → drain queue
    BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/environments/{id}/work/{workId}/stop
    BRIDGE->>SRV: POST /v1/environments/{id}/deregister
    BRIDGE->>BRIDGE: Clear bridge pointer file<br/>(unless perpetual mode)
    BRIDGE-->>REPL: Bridge closed

    Note over BRIDGE: ══ Crash Recovery ══
    Note over BRIDGE: On restart: read bridge-pointer-{dir}.json<br/>→ Try reconnect-in-place with stored IDs<br/>→ Fall back to fresh session if TTL expired
